<span class="name"><a name="120960"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#3:&nbsp;<font color=black><b></b> Author:&nbsp;<b>Jamond</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Location: Colorado Springs</font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=120960&amp;sid=ac61305d8cdbae20b74370429843ef52#120960"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Tue Mar 30, 2004 11:59 am</font><span class="gen"><br>
	<span class="gensmall">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;----</span><br>

<span class="postbody">Any focus that does the following:
<br />

<br />
<ol type="1"><li>Lowers the cast time (spell haste)
<br />
<li>Decreases the mana cost (mana preservation)
<br />
<li>Increases buff duration</ol>
<br />
Make sure that the spell effect is for BENEFICIAL spells.  For example, getting something with Preservation of Solusek won't do a damn thing with the Spiritual line of our spells. 
<br />

<br />
Here's a good link for all the focus effects in the game:  <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/focuslist.html" target="_blank" class="postlink">Focus Effects</a>.
<br />

<br />
Enjoy!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
	<center><hr width=80%></center>
